# Code Quality Non-Negotiables

## Zero suppression comments — always

Never add these to any production file in `src/`, `bazaar.php`, or `templates/`:

```
// phpcs:ignore
// phpcs:disable
// @phpstan-ignore
// @phpstan-ignore-next-line
```

If a linter flags something, **fix the code**. The only legitimate alternatives:

| Situation | Right fix |
|---|---|
| PHPCS rule is wrong for this entire file/pattern | Add a config-level `<exclude-pattern>` in `phpcs.xml` |
| PHPStan doesn't know about a WP method | Use a `stubs/` file and reference it in `phpstan.neon` `stubFiles:`, or rewrite the call to use a stubbed API |
| A native function isn't in stubs | Add it to `patchwork.json` `redefinable-internals` (for tests) |
| WP_REST_Request method missing from stubs | Use `$_SERVER` with `wp_unslash` + `sanitize_text_field` instead |

Test files in `tests/` are not scanned by PHPCS — no suppressions needed there either.

## Classmap autoload — regenerate after adding files

This project uses `"classmap": ["src/"]` in `composer.json`. **Any new file in `src/` is invisible to autoloading until the classmap is regenerated.**

```bash
php composer.phar dump-autoload --no-scripts
```

Run this after:
- Creating a new class, interface, or trait in `src/`
- Renaming or moving a file in `src/`

Symptom when missing: `Error: Class "Bazaar\MyNewClass" not found` at test time despite the file existing.

## CspPolicy::compile() — trim sources before concatenating

When building a `directive value` string, always trim the value *before* joining with the directive name. Trimming the outer string leaves internal whitespace intact:

```php
// ❌ Leading whitespace survives — "script-src   'self'"
$parts[] = trim( "$directive $sources" );

// ✅ Sources trimmed independently — "script-src 'self'"
$parts[] = $directive . ' ' . trim( (string) $sources );
```

## Release zip — always include the Composer autoloader

This plugin has **no runtime PHP dependencies**, but the Composer classmap autoloader (`vendor/autoload.php` + `vendor/composer/`) **must be in the zip**. Without it the plugin fatals on activation because `Bazaar\Plugin` is never defined.

The correct build process:

```bash
# 1. Build JS
npm run build

# 2. Generate production-only autoloader (strips all dev packages)
php composer.phar install --no-dev --no-scripts --classmap-authoritative

# 3. Zip using .distignore (which keeps vendor/ in)
bash bin/build-zip.sh
```

**Never** build the zip by hand-picking files with a manual exclude list — use `bin/build-zip.sh` which reads `.distignore`.

CI verifies this automatically: the `release-zip` job unzips the artifact and fails if `vendor/autoload.php` is missing or if any dev package directory is present.

## WareRegistryInterface — depend on the abstraction

`WareRegistry` is `final`. Any class that accepts it as a constructor parameter and needs to be unit-tested **must** type-hint `WareRegistryInterface`, not the concrete class, so tests can mock the interface.

```php
// ❌ Cannot be tested — WareRegistry is final
public function __construct( WareRegistry $registry ) { … }

// ✅ Mockable and still accepts the real WareRegistry
public function __construct( WareRegistryInterface $registry ) { … }
```
